headline: BigBear Stock Keeps Jumping After Defense Deal. It Could Be a Mini-Palantir.
summary: BigBear reported net income of $2.5 million, marking its second ever quarterly profit and the first since 2023.  Shares jumped 6.1% to $6.06 on Tuesday after being up 18% in the premarket, and was up another 5.6% at $6.40 premarket trading Wednesday.  The stock was up 28% this year and 214% over the last 12 months as of Monday’s close, buoyed by lucrative government contracts and the broader excitement around AI.
